# MyFavouriteAlbums for basic users 

## Prerequisites

	Web browser of choice  
	Link to MyFavouriteAlbums, provided [here](https://cholstro.shinyapps.io/shiny-music/)

## Navigating the User Interface (UI)

This tutorial will be focused on navigating MFA’s user interface to display different kinds of data analysis. No downloads or installation will be required for this section.

## MFA’s interface is simple. It is 

comprised of 5 different tabs, as  
shown here. To navigate to a tab,  
simply click on it.

## 

## Number One Albums

This tab shows you the top rated albums for   
a range of years as defined by the slider

To define a range of years:

* Click on the circular buttons on the left or

	right of the slider and drag it across the   
meter to define a range

* The meter is value-inclusive, which means   
  that it will also include the top album of the   
  year for the ‘range’

	

## Bands and Artists 

This tab will show you all of the albums belonging  
to a particular artist that you have logged into MFA,  
as well as including a total number of albums ranked  
and a mean rating

* Start by clicking on the dropdown menu  
  * This brings up an alphabetically  
    sorted list of bands and artists  
* Alternatively, click the *backspace* key and  
  begin typing the name of the band/artist   
  you have in mind   
* Click Submit

## 

## 

## Top Albums by Year 

This tab will show you a ranked list of all   
albums of a selected year

* Select a year  
  * This brings up a chronological list  
    of years  
* Alternatively, click the *backspace* key and  
  begin typing the year you intend to look at  
* Click Submit

## 

## Vinyl 

This tab shows information about  
vinyl ownership for the albums logged  
into MFA.

There is nothing to click here. To learn  
how to modify album entries, consider   
looking in Task Documentation  
(Advanced Users, Developers) for Windows

## Band Comparison

This tab allows you to plot information about two artists against each other on a graph comparing album ratings across time

* Start by clicking on the dropdown menu  
  for one artist  
  * This brings up an alphabetically  
    sorted list of bands and artists  
* Alternatively, click the *backspace* key and  
  begin typing the name of the band/artist   
  you have in mind   
* Repeat for the second artist  
* This should produce a graph of time (years) against album ratings (1-10)
